{"id": "EUVD-2022-55361", "enisaUuid": "3f8203cf-d9cf-3232-bcff-5d8cd80850cf", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nposix-cpu-timers: Cleanup CPU timers before freeing them during exec\n\nCommit 55e8c8eb2c7b (\"posix-cpu-timers: Store a reference to a pid not a\ntask\") started looking up tasks by PID when deleting a CPU timer.\n\nWhen a non-leader thread calls execve, it will switch PIDs with the leader\nprocess. Then, as it calls exit_itimers, posix_cpu_timer_del cannot find\nthe task because the timer still points out to the old PID.\n\nThat means that armed timers won't be disarmed, that is, they won't be\nremoved from the timerqueue_list. exit_itimers will still release their\nmemory, and when that list is later processed, it leads to a\nuse-after-free.\n\nClean up the timers from the de-threaded task before freeing them. This\nprevents a reported use-after-free.", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:47", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-18T03:31:14", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/541840859ace9c2ccebc32fa9e376c7bd3def490", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/9e255ed238fc67058df87b0388ad6d4b2ef3a2bd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e8cb6e8fd9890780f1bfcf5592889e1b879e779c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b2fc1723eb65abb83e00d5f011de670296af0b28", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e362359ace6f87c201531872486ff295df306d13", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50095"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50095"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0076d419-4dd9-3e17-bafc-13fbf1081f60", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "55e8c8eb2c7b6bf30e99423ccfe7ca032f498f59 <e8cb6e8fd9890780f1bfcf5592889e1b879e779c"}, {"id": "063a7613-f058-3724-ae5a-b3a3ff4012ea", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.7"}, {"id": "0e8d463c-9b4c-39fc-a504-b68e5373d43c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "55e8c8eb2c7b6bf30e99423ccfe7ca032f498f59 <541840859ace9c2ccebc32fa9e376c7bd3def490"}, {"id": "1bf9620c-2b0e-3bbf-999f-4ef1f67ccbdc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.0"}, {"id": "2f889ff7-bc79-3e94-a68b-53c189cafcca", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.137"}, {"id": "4436471f-5fb3-333f-87a6-6f748f86d32b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "55e8c8eb2c7b6bf30e99423ccfe7ca032f498f59 <b2fc1723eb65abb83e00d5f011de670296af0b28"}, {"id": "963e1cf6-f977-310c-bbb9-e8d84b410847", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.61"}, {"id": "a5d16d0a-9bbc-3c38-83e4-1c56315c3afd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.18"}, {"id": "ac6ae322-2479-379f-9dbb-cdd0cbb4ac72", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "55e8c8eb2c7b6bf30e99423ccfe7ca032f498f59 <e362359ace6f87c201531872486ff295df306d13"}, {"id": "af87cb07-23ae-393c-a530-d51b1a934957", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "d384b8b0-436e-327a-9e18-fb69215af8f8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19.2"}, {"id": "d3e2eed9-cc1e-3105-95c5-ffd6e8b96717", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "55e8c8eb2c7b6bf30e99423ccfe7ca032f498f59 <9e255ed238fc67058df87b0388ad6d4b2ef3a2bd"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "d9c66f1e-e850-3972-87f1-7700caedd7a9", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}